FUNCTIONS

Make a function to identify potential extreme (3*IQR) outliers to remove noise generated by errors during movement capture on the machine
Show code 
# Function to remove extreme outliers using 3 * IQR method
remove_extreme_outliers <- function(data, value_column, group_column) {
  data %>%
    group_by({{ group_column }}) %>%
    mutate(
      Q1 = quantile({{ value_column }}, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
      Q3 = quantile({{ value_column }}, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
      IQR = Q3 - Q1,
      lower_bound = Q1 - 3 * IQR,
      upper_bound = Q3 + 3 * IQR,
      is_outlier = if_else({{ value_column }} < lower_bound | {{ value_column }} > upper_bound, TRUE, FALSE)
    ) %>%
    ungroup()
}

Summary function for behaviour

Show code 
summarise_behavior <- function(data, group_var, vars) {
  out <- data %>%
    dplyr::group_by({{ group_var }}) %>%
    dplyr::summarise(
      dplyr::across(
        dplyr::all_of(vars),
        list(
          mean = ~mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
          sd   = ~sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
          se   = ~sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(dplyr::n())
        ),
        .names = "{.col}_{.fn}"
      )
    )
  print(knitr::kable(out, format = "pipe", digits = 3))
  invisible(out)
}

Wilcox plot function

Show code 
plot_with_wilcox <- function(data, y_var, group_var) {
  # Ensure the grouping variable is a factor
  group_sym <- rlang::ensym(group_var)
  data <- data %>% mutate(!!group_sym := as.factor(!!group_sym))
  
  # Get group levels and create comparisons vs "c"
  groups <- levels(data[[rlang::as_string(group_sym)]])
  
  # Check that "c" exists
  if (!"c" %in% groups) stop('"c" must be one of the group levels to compare against.')
  
  # Compare all other groups to "c" only
  comparisons <- lapply(setdiff(groups, "c"), function(g) c("c", g))
  
  ggplot(data, aes(x = !!group_sym, y = !!rlang::enquo(y_var))) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    stat_compare_means(
      method = "wilcox.test",
      comparisons = comparisons,
      label = "p.signif",
      hide.ns = FALSE
    ) +
    theme_pubr()
}

Stat test function

Show code 
run_stats <- function(data, formula, dataset_name) {
  response_var <- all.vars(formula)[1]
  group_var    <- all.vars(formula)[2]

  data[[group_var]] <- as.factor(data[[group_var]])
  data_clean <- dplyr::filter(data, !is.na(.data[[response_var]]), !is.na(.data[[group_var]]))

  v <- data_clean[[response_var]]
  n <- length(v)

  shapiro <- if (n >= 3 && n <= 5000) shapiro.test(v)
             else if (n > 5000)       shapiro.test(sample(v, 5000))
             else                     list(statistic = NA, p.value = NA)

  levene  <- tryCatch(car::leveneTest(formula, data = data_clean), error = function(e) NULL)
  kruskal <- tryCatch(kruskal.test(formula, data = data_clean),   error = function(e) NULL)

  out <- tibble::tibble(
    dataset_name         = dataset_name,
    shapiro_statistic    = unname(shapiro$statistic),
    shapiro_p_value      = shapiro$p.value,
    levene_F_value       = if (!is.null(levene))  levene$`F value`[1]                else NA_real_,
    levene_p_value       = if (!is.null(levene))  levene$`Pr(>F)`[1]                 else NA_real_,
    kruskal_H_statistic  = if (!is.null(kruskal)) as.numeric(kruskal$statistic)      else NA_real_,
    kruskal_df           = if (!is.null(kruskal)) as.numeric(kruskal$parameter)      else NA_real_,
    kruskal_p_value      = if (!is.null(kruskal)) kruskal$p.value                    else NA_real_
  ) |>
    tidyr::pivot_longer(-dataset_name, names_to = "test_metric", values_to = "value") |>
    dplyr::mutate(
      significance = dplyr::case_when(
        grepl("_p_value$", test_metric) & value < 0.001 ~ "***",
        grepl("_p_value$", test_metric) & value < 0.01  ~ "**",
        grepl("_p_value$", test_metric) & value < 0.05  ~ "*",
        TRUE ~ ""
      )
    )

  print(knitr::kable(out, format = "pipe", digits = 3))
  invisible(out)
}

Dunn test function

Show code 
run_dunn_test <- function(data, response, group, save_path = NULL, label = NULL) {
  formula <- as.formula(paste(response, "~", group))
  dunn <- FSA::dunnTest(formula, data = data, method = "bonferroni")

  dunn_df <- tibble::as_tibble(dunn$res) |>
    dplyr::rename(
      comparison   = Comparison,
      z_statistic  = Z,
      p_value      = P.unadj,
      p_adj        = P.adj
    ) |>
    tidyr::separate(comparison, into = c("group1", "group2"), sep = " - ", remove = FALSE) |>
    dplyr::mutate(
      significance = dplyr::case_when(
        p_adj < 0.001 ~ "***",
        p_adj < 0.01  ~ "**",
        p_adj < 0.05  ~ "*",
        TRUE ~ ""
      ),
      effect = dplyr::case_when(
        significance != "" & z_statistic < 0 ~ paste0("Positive (", group2, " > ", group1, ")"),
        significance != "" & z_statistic > 0 ~ paste0("Negative (", group1, " > ", group2, ")"),
        TRUE ~ ""
      )
    ) |>
    dplyr::select(-group1, -group2)

  if (!is.null(save_path) && !is.null(label)) {
    file_path <- file.path(save_path, paste0(label, "_", response, "_dunn.xlsx"))
    writexl::write_xlsx(dunn_df, file_path)
  }

  print(knitr::kable(dunn_df, format = "pipe", digits = 3))
  invisible(dunn_df)
}

# derive names
all_names      <- names(behavior_files_list)
byMin_names    <- all_names[stringr::str_detect(all_names, "_byMin$")]
activity_names <- all_names[stringr::str_detect(all_names, "_activity$")]

safe_print_plot <- function(p) { try(print(p), silent = TRUE); invisible(NULL) }

## Behavior (by minute)
purrr::walk(byMin_names, function(name) {
  data <- behavior_files_list[[name]] |>
  dplyr::mutate(exposure = relabel_levels(exposure))

  # outlier-cleaned (3*IQR)
  cleaned <- remove_extreme_outliers(data, velocity, exposure) |>
    dplyr::filter(!is_outlier) |>
    dplyr::select(-tidyselect::any_of(c("Q1","Q3","IQR","lower_bound","upper_bound","is_outlier"))) |>
    dplyr::mutate(exposure = droplevels(exposure))

  # quick Ns for callout
  n_raw   <- as.data.frame(table(data$exposure))    |> dplyr::rename(group = Var1, n_raw  = Freq)
  n_clean <- as.data.frame(table(cleaned$exposure)) |> dplyr::rename(group = Var1, n_clean= Freq)
  n_join  <- dplyr::left_join(n_raw, n_clean, by = "group")

 ## Section heading (in ToC) — remapped material + byMin → Distance/Velocity
 cat("\n\n### ", pretty_section_name(name), "\n\n", sep = "")

  ## Open tabset
  cat("::: {.panel-tabset}\n\n", sep = "")

  ## --- Stats tab ---
  cat("#### Stats\n\n", sep = "")
  cat("::: callout-note\n", sep = "")
  cat("**Groups:** ", paste(levels(cleaned$exposure), collapse = ", "), "\n\n", sep = "")
  cat("**N per group (raw → clean):**\n\n", sep = "")
  print(knitr::kable(n_join, format = "pipe"))
  cat("\n:::\n\n", sep = "")

  summarise_behavior(cleaned, exposure, c("velocity","distance_moved"))
  run_stats(cleaned, velocity ~ exposure,       name)
  run_stats(cleaned, distance_moved ~ exposure, name)
  run_dunn_test(cleaned, "velocity",       "exposure",
                save_path = "results_FINAL/Behavior/dunn_results", label = name)
  run_dunn_test(cleaned, "distance_moved", "exposure",
                save_path = "results_FINAL/Behavior/dunn_results", label = paste0(name,"_dist"))

  ## --- Plots tab ---
  cat("\n#### Plots\n\n", sep = "")
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(data,    velocity,        exposure))
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(data,    distance_moved,  exposure))
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(cleaned, velocity,        exposure))
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(cleaned, distance_moved,  exposure))

  ## --- Distributions tab ---
  cat("\n#### Distributions\n\n", sep = "")
  p_dens_v <- ggdensity(cleaned, x = "velocity", fill = "exposure",
                        add = "mean", rug = TRUE, color = "exposure") +
              facet_wrap(~ exposure) +
              labs(title = paste("Velocity density –", name))
  p_dens_d <- ggdensity(cleaned, x = "distance_moved", fill = "exposure",
                        add = "mean", rug = TRUE, color = "exposure") +
              facet_wrap(~ exposure) +
              labs(title = paste("Distance moved density –", name))
  safe_print_plot(p_dens_v); safe_print_plot(p_dens_d)

  ## close tabset
  cat("\n:::\n", sep = "")
})

## Activity
purrr::walk(activity_names, function(name) {
  data <- behavior_files_list[[name]] |>
  dplyr::mutate(Material = relabel_levels(Material))
  n_tbl <- as.data.frame(table(data$Material)) |> dplyr::rename(group = Var1, n = Freq)

## Section heading (in ToC) — remapped material; keep "activity" suffix
cat("\n\n### ", pretty_section_name(name), "\n\n", sep = "")

  ## Open tabset
  cat("::: {.panel-tabset}\n\n", sep = "")

  ## --- Stats tab ---
  cat("#### Stats\n\n", sep = "")
  cat("::: callout-note\n", sep = "")
  cat("**Groups:** ", paste(levels(data$Material), collapse = ", "), "\n\n", sep = "")
  cat("**N per group:**\n\n", sep = "")
  print(knitr::kable(n_tbl, format = "pipe"))
  cat("\n:::\n\n", sep = "")

  summarise_behavior(data, Material, c("Active_percent"))
  run_stats(data, Active_percent ~ Material, name)
  run_dunn_test(data, "Active_percent", "Material",
                save_path = "results_FINAL/Activity/dunn_results", label = name)

  ## --- Plots tab ---
  cat("\n#### Plots\n\n", sep = "")
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(data, Active_percent, Material))

  ## --- Distributions tab ---
  cat("\n#### Distributions\n\n", sep = "")
  p_dens <- ggdensity(data, x = "Active_percent", fill = "Material",
                      add = "mean", rug = TRUE, color = "Material") +
            facet_wrap(~ Material) +
            labs(title = paste("Active % density –", name))
  safe_print_plot(p_dens)

  ## close tabset
  cat("\n:::\n", sep = "")
})

```{r, echo=FALSE, results="hide", include=FALSE}
# ---- Label mapping & helpers ----
map_titles <- c(
  "ps_5"  = "PS MPs",
  "ps_01" = "PS NPs",
  "hdpe" = "PE MPs",
  "pen"  = "PE NPs"
)

# Relabel factor levels (for exposure/Material) without using !!!
relabel_levels <- function(f) {
  f <- as.factor(f)
  lv <- levels(f)
  idx <- match(lv, names(map_titles))
  repl <- !is.na(idx)
  lv[repl] <- unname(map_titles[idx[repl]])
  levels(f) <- lv
  f
}

pretty_section_name <- function(x) {
  # detect suffix
  has_bymin    <- grepl("_byMin$", x, ignore.case = TRUE)
  has_activity <- grepl("_activity$", x, ignore.case = TRUE)

  # strip the trailing suffix once to get the full base (can include underscores)
  base <- sub("_(byMin|activity)$", "", x, ignore.case = TRUE)

  # case-insensitive lookup in map_titles
  nm_low <- tolower(names(map_titles))
  idx    <- match(tolower(base), nm_low)
  mapped <- if (!is.na(idx)) unname(map_titles[idx]) else base

  # reattach suffix
  if (has_bymin) {
    paste0(mapped, " Distance/Velocity")
  } else if (has_activity) {
    paste0(mapped, "_activity")
  } else {
    mapped
  }
}
```

### FUNCTIONS
###### Make a function to identify potential extreme (3*IQR) outliers to remove noise generated by errors during movement capture on the machine
```{r}
# Function to remove extreme outliers using 3 * IQR method
remove_extreme_outliers <- function(data, value_column, group_column) {
  data %>%
    group_by({{ group_column }}) %>%
    mutate(
      Q1 = quantile({{ value_column }}, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
      Q3 = quantile({{ value_column }}, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
      IQR = Q3 - Q1,
      lower_bound = Q1 - 3 * IQR,
      upper_bound = Q3 + 3 * IQR,
      is_outlier = if_else({{ value_column }} < lower_bound | {{ value_column }} > upper_bound, TRUE, FALSE)
    ) %>%
    ungroup()
}
```

###  Summary function for behaviour
```{r}
summarise_behavior <- function(data, group_var, vars) {
  out <- data %>%
    dplyr::group_by({{ group_var }}) %>%
    dplyr::summarise(
      dplyr::across(
        dplyr::all_of(vars),
        list(
          mean = ~mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
          sd   = ~sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
          se   = ~sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(dplyr::n())
        ),
        .names = "{.col}_{.fn}"
      )
    )
  print(knitr::kable(out, format = "pipe", digits = 3))
  invisible(out)
}
```

### Wilcox plot function
```{r}
plot_with_wilcox <- function(data, y_var, group_var) {
  # Ensure the grouping variable is a factor
  group_sym <- rlang::ensym(group_var)
  data <- data %>% mutate(!!group_sym := as.factor(!!group_sym))
  
  # Get group levels and create comparisons vs "c"
  groups <- levels(data[[rlang::as_string(group_sym)]])
  
  # Check that "c" exists
  if (!"c" %in% groups) stop('"c" must be one of the group levels to compare against.')
  
  # Compare all other groups to "c" only
  comparisons <- lapply(setdiff(groups, "c"), function(g) c("c", g))
  
  ggplot(data, aes(x = !!group_sym, y = !!rlang::enquo(y_var))) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    stat_compare_means(
      method = "wilcox.test",
      comparisons = comparisons,
      label = "p.signif",
      hide.ns = FALSE
    ) +
    theme_pubr()
}
```

### Stat test function
```{r}
run_stats <- function(data, formula, dataset_name) {
  response_var <- all.vars(formula)[1]
  group_var    <- all.vars(formula)[2]

  data[[group_var]] <- as.factor(data[[group_var]])
  data_clean <- dplyr::filter(data, !is.na(.data[[response_var]]), !is.na(.data[[group_var]]))

  v <- data_clean[[response_var]]
  n <- length(v)

  shapiro <- if (n >= 3 && n <= 5000) shapiro.test(v)
             else if (n > 5000)       shapiro.test(sample(v, 5000))
             else                     list(statistic = NA, p.value = NA)

  levene  <- tryCatch(car::leveneTest(formula, data = data_clean), error = function(e) NULL)
  kruskal <- tryCatch(kruskal.test(formula, data = data_clean),   error = function(e) NULL)

  out <- tibble::tibble(
    dataset_name         = dataset_name,
    shapiro_statistic    = unname(shapiro$statistic),
    shapiro_p_value      = shapiro$p.value,
    levene_F_value       = if (!is.null(levene))  levene$`F value`[1]                else NA_real_,
    levene_p_value       = if (!is.null(levene))  levene$`Pr(>F)`[1]                 else NA_real_,
    kruskal_H_statistic  = if (!is.null(kruskal)) as.numeric(kruskal$statistic)      else NA_real_,
    kruskal_df           = if (!is.null(kruskal)) as.numeric(kruskal$parameter)      else NA_real_,
    kruskal_p_value      = if (!is.null(kruskal)) kruskal$p.value                    else NA_real_
  ) |>
    tidyr::pivot_longer(-dataset_name, names_to = "test_metric", values_to = "value") |>
    dplyr::mutate(
      significance = dplyr::case_when(
        grepl("_p_value$", test_metric) & value < 0.001 ~ "***",
        grepl("_p_value$", test_metric) & value < 0.01  ~ "**",
        grepl("_p_value$", test_metric) & value < 0.05  ~ "*",
        TRUE ~ ""
      )
    )

  print(knitr::kable(out, format = "pipe", digits = 3))
  invisible(out)
}
```

### Dunn test function
```{r}
run_dunn_test <- function(data, response, group, save_path = NULL, label = NULL) {
  formula <- as.formula(paste(response, "~", group))
  dunn <- FSA::dunnTest(formula, data = data, method = "bonferroni")

  dunn_df <- tibble::as_tibble(dunn$res) |>
    dplyr::rename(
      comparison   = Comparison,
      z_statistic  = Z,
      p_value      = P.unadj,
      p_adj        = P.adj
    ) |>
    tidyr::separate(comparison, into = c("group1", "group2"), sep = " - ", remove = FALSE) |>
    dplyr::mutate(
      significance = dplyr::case_when(
        p_adj < 0.001 ~ "***",
        p_adj < 0.01  ~ "**",
        p_adj < 0.05  ~ "*",
        TRUE ~ ""
      ),
      effect = dplyr::case_when(
        significance != "" & z_statistic < 0 ~ paste0("Positive (", group2, " > ", group1, ")"),
        significance != "" & z_statistic > 0 ~ paste0("Negative (", group1, " > ", group2, ")"),
        TRUE ~ ""
      )
    ) |>
    dplyr::select(-group1, -group2)

  if (!is.null(save_path) && !is.null(label)) {
    file_path <- file.path(save_path, paste0(label, "_", response, "_dunn.xlsx"))
    writexl::write_xlsx(dunn_df, file_path)
  }

  print(knitr::kable(dunn_df, format = "pipe", digits = 3))
  invisible(dunn_df)
}
```

```{r, echo=TRUE, results="asis"}
# derive names
all_names      <- names(behavior_files_list)
byMin_names    <- all_names[stringr::str_detect(all_names, "_byMin$")]
activity_names <- all_names[stringr::str_detect(all_names, "_activity$")]

safe_print_plot <- function(p) { try(print(p), silent = TRUE); invisible(NULL) }

## Behavior (by minute)
purrr::walk(byMin_names, function(name) {
  data <- behavior_files_list[[name]] |>
  dplyr::mutate(exposure = relabel_levels(exposure))

  # outlier-cleaned (3*IQR)
  cleaned <- remove_extreme_outliers(data, velocity, exposure) |>
    dplyr::filter(!is_outlier) |>
    dplyr::select(-tidyselect::any_of(c("Q1","Q3","IQR","lower_bound","upper_bound","is_outlier"))) |>
    dplyr::mutate(exposure = droplevels(exposure))

  # quick Ns for callout
  n_raw   <- as.data.frame(table(data$exposure))    |> dplyr::rename(group = Var1, n_raw  = Freq)
  n_clean <- as.data.frame(table(cleaned$exposure)) |> dplyr::rename(group = Var1, n_clean= Freq)
  n_join  <- dplyr::left_join(n_raw, n_clean, by = "group")

 ## Section heading (in ToC) — remapped material + byMin → Distance/Velocity
 cat("\n\n### ", pretty_section_name(name), "\n\n", sep = "")

  ## Open tabset
  cat("::: {.panel-tabset}\n\n", sep = "")

  ## --- Stats tab ---
  cat("#### Stats\n\n", sep = "")
  cat("::: callout-note\n", sep = "")
  cat("**Groups:** ", paste(levels(cleaned$exposure), collapse = ", "), "\n\n", sep = "")
  cat("**N per group (raw → clean):**\n\n", sep = "")
  print(knitr::kable(n_join, format = "pipe"))
  cat("\n:::\n\n", sep = "")

  summarise_behavior(cleaned, exposure, c("velocity","distance_moved"))
  run_stats(cleaned, velocity ~ exposure,       name)
  run_stats(cleaned, distance_moved ~ exposure, name)
  run_dunn_test(cleaned, "velocity",       "exposure",
                save_path = "results_FINAL/Behavior/dunn_results", label = name)
  run_dunn_test(cleaned, "distance_moved", "exposure",
                save_path = "results_FINAL/Behavior/dunn_results", label = paste0(name,"_dist"))

  ## --- Plots tab ---
  cat("\n#### Plots\n\n", sep = "")
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(data,    velocity,        exposure))
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(data,    distance_moved,  exposure))
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(cleaned, velocity,        exposure))
  safe_print_plot(plot_with_wilcox(cleaned, distance_moved,  exposure))

  ## --- Distributions tab ---
  cat("\n#### Distributions\n\n", sep = "")
  p_dens_v <- ggdensity(cleaned, x = "velocity", fill = "exposure",
                        add = "mean", rug = TRUE, color = "exposure") +
              facet_wrap(~ exposure) +
              labs(title = paste("Velocity density –", name))
  p_dens_d <- ggdensity(cleaned, x = "distance_moved", fill = "exposure",
                        add = "mean", rug = TRUE, color = "exposure") +
              facet_wrap(~ exposure) +
              labs(title = paste("Distance moved density –", name))
  safe_print_plot(p_dens_v); safe_print_plot(p_dens_d)

  ## close tabset
  cat("\n:::\n", sep = "")
})

## Section heading (in ToC) — remapped material; keep "activity" suffix
cat("\n\n### ", pretty_section_name(name), "\n\n", sep = "")

  ## Open tabset
```
